# Wakfu Auto-Builder

## Objective

This is a **prototype equipment optimizer for the MMORPG Wakfu**. Given user-defined constraints (minimum stats, level cap, rarity filters) and an optimization target (maximize mastery), it uses **mixed-integer linear programming** (OR-Tools CBC solver) to find the optimal set of 14 equipment pieces.

The project originated from this Wakfu [forum post](https://www.wakfu.com/fr/forum/8-discussions-generales/429089-prototype-builder-presentation-concept).

## Tech Stack

- **Python 3.12+**
- **PySide6 / Qt QML** — GUI framework. Python models are exposed to QML via `@QmlElement`.
- **Google OR-Tools** (`ortools.linear_solver.pywraplp`) — MIP solver for equipment optimization.
- Game data is stored as **static JSON files** in `data/1.78.1.7/`.

## Architecture

```
main.py                         # Entry point: QGuiApplication + QML engine
├── settings.py                 # Global state (enums, data dicts, solver variables)
├── wakutils.py                 # JSON parsing, item restructuring, weapon type tagging
├── solver.py                   # Constraint builder functions (LP helpers)
├── constraint.py               # Constraint class hierarchy (Constraint, ResConstraint, etc.)
│
├── wakfuConstraintSelector.py  # Core logic: builds solver model, runs optimization
├── wakfuConstraintSelectorTemplate.py  # QAbstractListModel for constraint UI
├── wakfuitemlist.py            # QAbstractListModel for result item list
├── wakfuItemDetail.py          # QAbstractListModel for single item stats
├── wakfuItemStatSum.py         # QAbstractListModel for aggregated stats
│
├── views/
│   ├── mainPage.qml            # Root window (switches between ConstraintGrid and Resultitem)
│   ├── ConstraintGrid.qml      # Main constraint editing page + Solve button
│   ├── ConstraintSelector.qml  # Single constraint input (text + number field)
│   ├── MaximizeConstraintSelector.qml   # Toggle for mastery maximize targets
│   ├── MaximizeRatioConstraintSelector.qml  # (extends MaximizeConstraintSelector)
│   └── Resultitem.qml          # Result page: item list, item detail popup, stat summary
│
└── data/1.78.1.7/
    ├── items.json               # All equipment items
    ├── itemProperties.json      # Item property definitions
    ├── equipmentItemTypes.json  # Equipment slot/type definitions
    └── actions.json             # Stat action definitions (mastery, res, etc.)
```

## Data Flow

1. **Startup** (`main.py`): `settings.initGlobal()` initializes global dicts, then `wakutils.setupJson()` parses JSON files, restructures items into ID-keyed maps, and tags weapon types.
2. **Constraint editing** (QML `ConstraintGrid`): User sets level, rarity, stat constraints and mastery maximize targets. Values are stored in `WakfuConstraintSelectorTemplate` models and bound two-way via QML.
3. **Solve** (`WakfuConstraintSelector.solve()`): Filters items by level/rarity, creates boolean variables in OR-Tools, adds slot/rarity/weapon constraints, adds user stat constraints, sets mastery maximization objective, then calls `solver.Solve()`.
4. **Results** (QML `Resultitem`): Displays optimal item list (left pane), item detail on hover, and aggregated stats (right pane).

## Key Global State (`settings.py`)

All shared data lives in `settings` module globals:
- `ITEMS_DATA` — dict of items keyed by item ID (after restructuring)
- `EQUIPMENT_ITEM_TYPES_DATA` — equipment type definitions keyed by ID
- `ACTION_DATA` — action definitions keyed by ID
- `VARIABLES` — dict of OR-Tools `BoolVar` keyed by item ID (rebuilt each solve)
- `OPTIMIZED_ITEM_LIST` — result list of `{id, name}` dicts

## Constraint Hierarchy (`constraint.py`)

- `Constraint` — base class, creates `>=` constraint from simple add/subtract action pairs
- `LevelConstraint` / `RarityConstraint` — filtering only (no solver constraints, handled in `initSolver`)
- `ResConstraint` — resistance target: converts % reduction to raw res via log formula, constrains all 4 elements
- `MasteryConstraint` — included in maximize objective, not as a minimum bound
- `RatioConstraint` — weighted contribution to maximize objective

## Conventions

- All solver helper functions are in `solver.py` and operate on `settings.VARIABLES` / `settings.ITEMS_DATA`.
- QML models inherit `QAbstractListModel` and are registered with `@QmlElement`.
- Stat IDs match Wakfu's internal `actionId` system (see `simpleActionEnum`, `paramsActionEnum`).
- The project uses **flat file structure** (no packages/submodules).

## Running

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
python main.py
```

Dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt` (PySide6, ortools).
